Package Modele

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Observer
    This is the Observer interface implementing the Observer design pattern.
    Score
    This interface implements the Visitor design pattern, used by visitable classes
    Strategie
    This interface implements the Strategy design pattern, used for virtual players to adopt different behaviours.
    Visitor
    This interface implements the Visitor design pattern
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Carte
    This class defines the different types of cards used in the game, and their possible actions.
    CompteurDeScore1
    This class is a Visitor designed to calculate player's jest scores.
    CompteurDeScore2
    This class implements the Visitor design pattern.
    Conditions
    This class represents the condition inscribed at the bottom of each card, for whenever it is a trophy card.
    Difficile
    This class implements the design pattern Strategie.
    Facile
    This class implements the Visitor design pattern.
    Jest
    This class represents the Jest in the game.
    Joker
    This class represents the joker card in the game.
    Joueur
    This class represents the player and is the superclass of the Virtual and Physical player.
    JoueurPhys
    Inherits from the Joueur, doesn't implement any methods but instead call methods from the superclass.
    JoueurVirt
    This class inherits from Joueur and is the main user of the Strategy design pattern.
    Main
    This class represents the hand of the player, it is a distinction between a player having cards, and a hand containing those cards.
    Observable
    This is the Observable class used in the Observer design pattern.
    Partie
    The core of the game, the Partie class inherits Observable and is where the game plays on console and a major part of it is used for the GUI interaction.
    Pioche
    This class inherits from the Tas, which is a composition of Cartes
    SuitCards
    This is the subclass of the class Cartes, it's main purpose is to display descriptions of suit cards on the console
    Tas
    This class is the superclass for all collections of cards, it contains a list of cards and is observable.
    Trophee
    This class represents the trophy, it contains an array of 2 cards which are the trophies.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    action
    This enumeration stores the actions needed to get the trophy.
    suits
    This enumeration contains all the suits used in the game
